data.title: EastEnders Star Jessie Wallace Shares Rare Snap Of Fiancé
data.meta_description: EastEnders Jessie Wallace had her admirers and co-stars showering her with compliments when she shared a photo of her seldom-seen fiancé.
data.text:
Jessie Wallace had fans showering her with compliments after she shared a rare photo of her seldom-seen fiancé this week.

The 51-year-old soap star and her partner Justin Gallwey went public with their romance last year but have known each other since their teenage years.

Today's top videos

In February, Jessie, who plays Kat Slater on the soap, joyfully confirmed her engagement to the carpenter.

Despite keeping her personal life relatively discreet, Jessie gave her fans a delightful surprise on Wednesday by posting a heartwarming selfie of herself and her fiancé.

Sharing the intimate moment, the veteran TV star who made her EastEnders debut in 2000, radiated happiness as she cuddled close to her partner.

Jessie accompanied the photo with a cascade of heart emojis as the caption, prompting her fans to fill the comments section with expressions of joy for the couple.

One fan remarked, 'Gorgeous pic of you both,' while another chimed in, 'You two make my heart melt.' A third wrote, 'Love that smile of yours gal keep it up xxx'

Even her EastEnders co-stars joined the chorus of admiration. Balvinder Sopal, who portrays Suki Panesar, described them as 'Beautiful people.'

Earlier this year, The Sun on Sunday reported the news of their engagement, stating that the couple were set to tie the knot after a year of dating.

A close source told the outlet, 'Jessie has been proudly wearing the ring.'

Further confirmation came from Jessie herself as she shared a sunny snapshot of her and her future husband, captioned 'My fiancé and moi.'

Fans were ecstatic, with one writing, 'Congratulations to you both you suit happy it beams out of you.'
